  "articleSummary": "This article frames ReDoS (Regular Expression Denial-of-Service) as a security vulnerability, not merely a performance issue, caused by poorly written or implemented regular expressions that can exhaust CPU/memory with crafted user input. It identifies warning signs such as nested quantifiers, backtracking-heavy engines, and unchecked input on hot request paths. Mitigations include bounding input length, adding timeouts, using static analysis, or switching to non-backtracking engines. The tone is a tutorial-style security analysis, aimed at developers and security engineers, and emphasizes that ReDoS belongs in a threat model.",
